<p>Hello that is my homework from the course for begginers, and I have no idea how to take the first input i than the second, not the numbers typed but the simple i. e.g.</p>  <p>2   3 4    4 3   1</p>  <p>I want to separate them somehow. But with this code it only takes :</p>  <p>1 1   2 3   4   4etc.. And the source.</p>  <pre><code> Console.Write("Enter number of the numbers: ");         int a = int.Parse(Console.ReadLine());         int[] numbers = new int[a];         int even = 1;         int odd = 1;         for (int i = 0; i &lt; a; i++)         {             numbers[i] = int.Parse(Console.ReadLine());             if (numbers[i] % 2 == 0)             {                 even *= numbers[i];             }             else if (numbers[i] % 2 !=0)             {                 odd *= numbers[i];             }          }         Console.WriteLine(odd);         Console.WriteLine(even); </code></pre>